'''Annabella Avery Thorne'''<ref name="AllMusic Bio"/> (born October 8, 1997) is an American actress and singer. She began her career appearing as a child model. Thorne played Ruthy Spivey in the television series ''[[My Own Worst Enemy (TV series)|My Own Worst Enemy]]'' (2008) and Tancy Henrickson in the fourth season of ''[[Big Love (TV series)|Big Love]]'' (2010),  before gaining prominence for her role as [[CeCe Jones]] on the [[Disney Channel]] series ''[[Shake It Up (U.S. TV series)|Shake It Up]]'' (2010–2013).<ref name=auto-tune>{{cite web |author=Tehrene Firman |title=Bella Thorne Refuses to Auto-Tune Her Music Like Other Disney Stars |url=http://www.j-14.com/posts/bella-thorne-refuses-to-auto-tune-her-music-like-other-disney-stars-38559 |publisher=J-14 |accessdate=September 28, 2014}}</ref> She also portrayed the lead role of Paige Townsen in the [[Freeform (TV network)|Freeform]] drama series ''[[Famous in Love]]'' (2017–2018). She has also appeared in several films, including ''[[Blended (film)|Blended]]'' (2014), ''[[The DUFF]]'' (2015), ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Road Chip]]'' (2015), ''[[You Get Me (film)|You Get Me]]'' (2017), ''[[Amityville: The Awakening]]'' (2017), ''[[The Babysitter (2017 film)|The Babysitter]]'' (2017), ''[[Midnight Sun (2018 film)|Midnight Sun]]'' (2018) and ''[[Assassination Nation]]'' (2018).

==Early life and education==
Thorne was born in [[Pembroke Pines, Florida]], to Tamara Thorne (née Beckett)<ref name=ElevenTalent-TamaraThorne>{{cite web |title=Tamara Thorne |url=http://eleventalent.com/#tab-1475383719072-9 |website=Eleven Talent Agency}}</ref> and Delancey Reinaldo "Rey" Thorne.<ref name="Disney Channel Medianet"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.belladogmagazine.com/dog-news/277-bella-thorne |title=Meet Young Star and Rescue Volunteer Bella Thorne |publisher=BellaDOG Magazine |accessdate=August 17, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109030725/http://www.belladogmagazine.com/dog-news/277-bella-thorne |archive-date=November 9, 2014 |dead-url=yes  }}</ref> She has three siblings who are also actors.<ref name="Disney Channel Medianet"/><ref>Lee Hernandez (July 6, 2011). [http://www.latina.com/entertainment/buzz/exclusive-bella-thorne-wants-her-shake-it-character-be-cuban "EXCLUSIVE: Bella Thorne Wants Her ‘Shake It Up!’ Character to be Cuban!"]. ''[[Latina (magazine)|Latina]]''; accessed January 7, 2016.</ref> Her father, who died in 2007 in a traffic accident,<ref name=SunSentinel-Father-Obit-2007>{{cite news |title=Delancey Rey Thorne's Obituary on Sun-Sentinel |url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/sunsentinel/obituary.aspx?n=delancey-rey-thorne&pid=87358682 |work=[[Sun-Sentinel]] |date=April 20, 2007}}</ref><ref name=MiamiHerald-AutumnFalls-2014>{{cite news |last1=Marr |first1=Madeleine |title=Actress Bella Thorne signing copies of 'Autumn Falls' |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/entertainment/celebrities/article3931459.html |work=[[Miami Herald]] |date=November 14, 2014 |language=en}}</ref> was [[Cubans|Cuban]].<ref name=InTouchWeekly-AboutDyingAlone-2017>{{cite news |last1=Isaac |first1=Paulina Jayne |title=Bella Thorne Pens a Song "About Dying Alone" in Honor of Her Late Father |url=http://www.intouchweekly.com/posts/bella-thorne-dad-died-137374 |work=[[In Touch Weekly]] |date=July 21, 2017}}</ref><ref name=USWeekly-AutumnFalls-2014>{{cite news |last1=Yahoo! Celebrity Staff |title=Bella Thorne Explains Sharing Her Father's Death and More in New Book |url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/bella-thorne-explains-sharing-her-fathers-death-and-more-in-new-book-20141311 |work=[[US Weekly]] |date=November 13, 2014}}</ref> On her maternal side, Thorne said she is of [[Italians|Italian]] ancestry, with some [[Irish people|Irish]], [[English people|English]], [[Welsh people|Welsh]], and [[German people|German]] descent.<ref name=HuffPo-ShakeItUp-2012>{{cite news |last1=Hernandez |first1=Lee |title='Shake It Up' Star Bella Thorne On Being Cuban: 'A Lot Of People Think I'm Lying' (EXCLUSIVE) |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/06/27/shake-it-up-star-bella-thorne_n_1628476.html |work=[[The Huffington Post]] |date=June 27, 2012}}</ref> Thorne has said that she was raised by a single mother who was supporting four children, and that they were very poor, which is why she worked as a child actor, to help to support the family.<ref name=Refinery29-HappySadConfused-2017>{{cite news |last1=Midkiff |first1=Sarah |title=Bella Thorne Said She Took Her Disney Role To Save Her Family From Homelessness |url=http://www.refinery29.com/2017/04/151182/bella-thorne-disney-family-homelessness |work=[[Refinery29]] |date=April 22, 2017}}</ref>

On a September 2017 appearance on ''[[Chelsea (TV series)|Chelsea]],'' Thorne told [[Chelsea Handler]] that she was bullied growing up because she was dyslexic, lived in a suburban area and spoke [[Spanish language|Spanish]] as her [[native language]].<ref name=HarpersBazaar-FamousInLove-2017>{{cite news |last1=Fleming |first1=Olivia |title=Bella Thorne on Fame, Love, and Life After Disney |url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/features/a21702/bella-thorne-interview-marilyn-monroe/ |work=[[Harper's Bazaar]] |date=April 12, 2017 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=ChelseaShow-2017>{{cite news |last1=Handler |first1=Chelsea |last2=Thorne |first2=Bella |title=Why not make the world a little bit kinder? @bellathorne is now streaming on @netflix |url=https://twitter.com/Chelseashow/status/906248299899797504 |work=[[Chelsea (TV series)|Chelsea]] |publisher=[[Netflix]] |date=September 8, 2017}}</ref>

In January 2018, Thorne stated that she had been sexually abused from a young age until she was 14.  She did not identify her abuser.<ref>"Fans rally around Bella Thorne after sexual abuse revelation," CNN, January 9, 2018 http://www.cnn.com/2018/01/09/entertainment/bella-thorne-sexual-abuse/index.html</ref>

Thorne was diagnosed with [[dyslexia]] in the first grade. She was [[home-schooled]] after previously attending a public school, where she had suffered from bullying. She improved in her learning after attending a [[Sylvan Learning]] center and began reading and writing a grade ahead.<ref name="Bella Thorne: Dancing Queen"/><ref name="Film Monthly.com"/> She discussed her dyslexia in an April 2010 interview with ''[[American Cheerleader]]'' magazine and explained that she overcame her dyslexia by rigorously reading everything she could find, including the labels of cereal boxes.<ref name="American Cheerleader Magazine"/><ref name="OceanUp.com 2"/>

==Career==

===2003–2009: ''Dirty Sexy Money'' and ''My Own Worst Enemy''===
[[File:Bella Thorne 2010.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Thorne at Variety's Power of Youth, in 2010.]]
Thorne's first film appearance was an uncredited role as a sidelines fan in the 2003 film ''[[Stuck on You (film)|Stuck on You]]''. She has since appeared in film and television projects including [[Entourage (U.S. TV series)|''Entourage'']] and ''[[The O.C.]]'' as a younger version of [[Taylor Townsend (The O.C.)|Taylor Townsend]]. In 2007, she joined the recurring cast of ''[[Dirty Sexy Money]]''{{'}}s second season, her first major television role. She played Margaux Darling. The series revolves around lawyer and family man Nick George when Nick's father mysteriously dies in a plane crash, he agrees to take his position as the Darling family's lawyer, while trying to discover who committed the murder.<ref name="Bella Thorne Interview"/> In 2008, Thorne starred alongside [[Christian Slater]] and [[Taylor Lautner]] in the short-lived drama series [[My Own Worst Enemy (TV series)|''My Own Worst Enemy'']], for which she won a [[Young Artist Awards 2010|Young Artist's Award]] for her portrayal of the character Ruthy Spivey; Thorne described her ''Enemy'' casting as a major breakthrough as this was the first recurring role in her career. That same year, she starred in the third-last episode of ''[[October Road (TV series)|October Road]]'' as Angela Ferilli, the pre-adolescence crush of the main characters. Her older brother Remy also guest-starred in the same episode as a younger [[Eddie Latekka]].{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}

In 2009, she starred the [[web series]] ''[[Little Monk]]'', which depicted characters from the series ''[[Monk (TV series)|Monk]]'', as Wendy, one of the Monks' classmates.  The webisodes are available only on the "Best of Monk" DVD. Also in 2009, she played the role of the vengeful antagonist in the horror film ''[[Forget Me Not (2009 film)|Forget Me Not]]''. Thorne took on a supporting role in the family drama ''[[Raspberry Magic]]'', the movie premiered at the [[Cinequest Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cinequest.org/media/CQ20Guide.pdf |title=Mavericks: Official Guide to Cinequest Film Festival 20 |date=March 7, 2010 |accessdate=January 26, 2011 |page=46}}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=Jennica |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and the [[San Francisco International Asian American Film Festival]] in 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://filmguide.festival.asianamericanmedia.org/tixSYS/2010/filmguide/Director/PP |title=Events by director: detail view |work=2010 San Francisco Asian American Film Festival |accessdate=January 26, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150912104538/http://filmguide.festival.asianamericanmedia.org/tixSYS/2010/filmguide/Director/PP |archivedate=September 12, 2015}}</ref>

===2010–13: ''Big Love'' and ''Shake It Up''===
[[File:Bella Thorne 4, 2012.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Thorne in 2012]]
In 2010, Thorne replaced Jolean Wejbe as Tancy "Teenie" Henrickson, Bill and Barb's younger daughter in Season 4 of HBO's ''[[Big Love]]''.<ref>{{cite news |author=Nellie Andreeva |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/televisionNews/idUSTRE58318T20090904 |title=Big Love gives bigger role to Bella Thorne |publisher=Reuters |date=September 4, 2009 |accessdate=April 27, 2010}}</ref> Thorne starred as co-star on the [[Disney Channel]] sitcom ''[[Shake It Up (U.S. TV series)|Shake It Up]]'', originally titled ''Dance, Dance Chicago''. Thorne played CeCe Jones, a dancer with heavy ambitions for a career in the spotlight despite having [[dyslexia]].<ref name="Variety.com"/> The show is a [[buddy comedy]] centered on a teen dance show (in a show-within-a-show format) co-starring Thorne and [[Zendaya]].<ref name="OceanUp.com"/> The multi-camera series began production in Hollywood, California, in July 2010 and premiered on November 7, 2010, on Disney Channel. While she had a substantial portfolio of work in television and film, Thorne had no experience in professional dancing before being cast. After signing onto the show in October 2009, she began taking three dance classes every night.<ref name="Bella Thorne: Dancing Queen"/> Thorne's first single, ''[[Watch Me (Bella Thorne and Zendaya song)|Watch Me]]'' was released on June 21, reaching 86 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] charts,<ref name="allmusic">{{cite web |url=http://allmusic.com/artist/bella-thorne-p2435050/charts-awards/billboard-singles |title=Billboard Chart History: Watch Me |work=Billboard |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref> 9 on the US [[Top Heatseekers]] charts<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2011-07-30/heatseekers-songs |title=Top Heatseekers Songs - Week of July 30, 2011 |date=July 30, 2010 |work=Billboard |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref> and earning [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]: Gold.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=zendaya&format=&go=Search&perPage=50 |title=US certifications: Zendaya |publisher=Recording Industry Association of America |accessdate=October 17, 2012}}</ref> On September 29, 2011, Disney Channel announced it had increased ''Shake It Up''{{'}}s second season order to 26 episodes.<ref>[{{cite web |author=Nellie Andreeva |url=http://www.deadline.com/2011/09/disney-channel-greenlights-comedy-pilot-gives-two-series-backup-orders/ |title=Disney Channel Greenlights Pilot About Talking Dog, Gives 2 Series Back Orders] |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=September 29, 2011 |access-date=March 25, 2017}}</ref> A 90-minute special episode ''[[List of Shake It Up episodes#ep49|Made In Japan]]'' aired August 17, 2012, as the season two finale.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tv.msn.com/tv/episode/shake-it-up!/made-in-japan |title=Shake it Up! - 'Made in Japan' Episode Info |publisher=TV.MSN.com |accessdate=April 7, 2012}}</ref>

On June 4, 2012, Disney Channel announced that ''Shake It Up'' had been renewed for a third season.<ref name="DCPRS3">{{cite web |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2012/06/04/disney-channel-orders-third-season-of-top-rated-dance-driven-series-shake-it-up-708211/20120604disney01 |title=Disney Channel Orders Third Season of Top Rated, Dance-Driven Series "Shake It Up" |date=June 4, 2012 |last=Disney Channel press release |publisher=The Futon Critic |accessdate=January 7, 2016}}</ref> In 2012, Thorne was cast as Avalon Greene in the [[List of Disney Channel Original Movies|Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Frenemies (film)|Frenemies]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tv.disney.go.com/disneychannel/originalmovies/frenemies/ |title=Disney Channel: Frenemies}}</ref> ''[[TTYLXOX]]'' was released on March 6, reaching 97 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] charts.<ref name="bill">{{cite web |url={{BillboardURLbyName |artist=bella thorne |chart=all}}|title=Ttylxox - Bella Thorne|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=March 29, 2012}}</ref> On March 30, 2013, it was confirmed by [[Hollywood Records]] via [[Twitter]] that Thorne had officially signed to the record label.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2013/03/29/bella-thorne-signs-on-with-hollywood-records |title=Bella Thorne Signs On With Hollywood Records |publisher=Disney Dreaming |date=March 29, 2013 |accessdate=April 1, 2014}}</ref> On July 25, 2013, the [[Disney Channel]] confirmed that ''Shake It Up'' would be canceled after the end of the third season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2013/07/26/shake-it-up-canceled-after-season-3 |title="Shake It Up" Canceled After Season 3 |publisher=Disney Dreaming |accessdate=May 21, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/07/25/shake-it-up-canceled_n_3655320.html |title='Shake It Up' Canceled: Disney Channel Will End Zendaya And Bella Thorne's Show After Season 3 |work=[[The Huffington Post]] |author=Jaimie Etkin |date=July 25, 2013 |accessdate=}}</ref> On April 23, 2013, Thorne announced her debut album with eleven songs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/03/28/bella-thorne-hints-at-her-debut-album-title |title=Bella Thorne Hints At Her Debut Album Title |publisher=Disney Dreaming |date=March 28, 2014}}</ref><ref name="dancingqueen219 says: I’m not a big fan of her music">{{cite web |author=dancingqueen219 says: I’m not a big fan of her music. |url=http://www.bopandtigerbeat.com/2013/04/bella-thorne-discusses-her-debut-album |title=Bella Thorne Discusses Her Debut Album! |publisher=Bopandtigerbeat.com |date=April 23, 2013 |accessdate=April 1, 2014}}</ref> Thorne spoke about the album, saying "What fans can expect is [for it] just to be very different from anyone because I don't like to be one of those artists where you can be like: 'Oh yeah, I know them from that song.' All my songs are very different from each other. So I don't want to be known as only one genre."<ref name="dancingqueen219 says: I’m not a big fan of her music"/> Thorne cited [[Britney Spears]], [[Kesha]], and [[Destiny's Child]] as influences for the album.<ref name=contactmusic>{{cite web |author=<!-- Staff report --> |url=http://www.contactmusic.com/story/bella-thorne-s-debut-album-will-suit-everyone_4065517 |title=Bella Thorne &#124; Bella Thorne's debut album will suit everyone |website=Contactmusic.com |date=February 13, 2014 |accessdate=April 1, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://tune.pk/video/5353472/bella-thorne-tour-details-favorite-music-behind-the-scenes-interview |title=Bella Thorne Tour Details Favorite Music! - Behind the Scenes Interview |website=Tune.pk |date=December 10, 2014 |accessdate=January 8, 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151122215754/http://tune.pk/video/5353472/bella-thorne-tour-details-favorite-music-behind-the-scenes-interview |archivedate=November 22, 2015 }}</ref>

===2014–present: Films, ''Famous in Love'', and upcoming debut album===
[[File:Bella Thorne 2, 2012.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Thorne at the [[Imagen Awards]] in 2012]]
In 2014, Thorne co-starred in the comedy ''[[Blended (film)|Blended]]'', as [[Adam Sandler]]'s character's daughter.<ref name=Blended>{{cite web |url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/05/bella-thorne-blended-movie-casting-adam-sandler-drew-barrymore |title=Disney Channel's Bella Thorne Stuck With Adam Sandler & Drew Barrymore In 'Blended' |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=May 3, 2013}}</ref> She also co-starred in the films ''[[Alexander and the Terrible, Horrible, No Good, Very Bad Day (film)|Alexander and the Terrible, Horrible, No Good, Very Bad Day]]'' (2014) and ''[[The DUFF]]'' (2015), playing high school antagonists.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thewrap.com/bella-thorne-star-teen-comedy-duff-cbs-films-exclusive |title=Bella Thorne to Co-Star in Teen Comedy 'The DUFF' for CBS Films (Exclusive) - TheWrap |work=TheWrap |accessdate=October 9, 2014}}</ref> On July 30, Thorne was cast in an episode of the fifteenth season of the ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/564637/bella-thorne-books-guest-role-on-csi-find-out-who-she-ll-play |title=Bella Thorne Books Guest Role on CSI—Find Out Who She'll Play |date=July 30, 2014 |publisher=E Online |accessdate=July 30, 2014}}</ref> The episode, "The Book of Shadows", aired October 19, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://au.ibtimes.com/articles/570282/20141021/csi-crime-scene-investigation-las-vegas-nick.htm |title='CSI Crime Scene Investigation' Season 15 Recap: Episode 4 'The Book of Shadows' Aired On October 19, 2014, The 'CSI Las Vegas' Team Investigates A Dangerous Science Experiment |date=October 21, 2014 |publisher=International Business Times |accessdate=October 23, 2014}}</ref> Thorne appeared in the sequel to ''[[Mostly Ghostly (film)|Mostly Ghostly]]'' (2008), titled ''[[Mostly Ghostly: Have You Met My Ghoulfriend]]'' (2014) as Cammy Cahill.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://parade.com/332916/scottneumyer/exclusive-clip-bloopers-from-the-set-of-r-l-stines-mostly-ghostly-have-you-met-my-ghoulfriend/|work=Parade|title=Exclusive Clip: Bloopers From the Set of R.L. Stine’s Mostly Ghostly: Have You Met My Ghoulfriend?|author=Scott Neumyer|date=August 28, 2014}}</ref> On October 15, Thorne revealed her debut album was canceled, saying she wasn't happy with the "auto-tuned bad music" she had in the works.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bella Thorne Never Wanted to Be a Singer |url=http://www.j-14.com/posts/bella-thorne-never-wanted-to-be-a-singer-55126 |website=J-14 |accessdate=June 1, 2015}}</ref> She released an EP, ''[[Jersey (EP)|Jersey]]'', on November 17.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.josepvinaixa.com/blog/bella-thorne-jersey-ep-cover |title=Bella Thorne: jersey EP official cover |work=Ultimate Music |accessdate=May 13, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018120421/http://www.josepvinaixa.com/blog/bella-thorne-jersey-ep-cover/ |archivedate=October 18, 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://celebrityselfies.net/bella-thorne-instagram-so-excited-to-let-you-know-that-im-releasing-my-ep-jersey-on-1117-httpt-cokuxiokdxgc |title=SO EXCITED TO LET YOU KNOW THAT I'M RELEASING MY EP #JERSEY ON 11/17 |work=Celebrity Selfies |accessdate=May 13, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141020023246/http://celebrityselfies.net/bella-thorne-instagram-so-excited-to-let-you-know-that-im-releasing-my-ep-jersey-on-1117-httpt-cokuxiokdxgc/ |archivedate=October 20, 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Virginia Van de Wall |title=Bella Thorne Announces Her New EP "Jersey" |url=http://www.j-14.com/posts/bella-thorne-announces-her-new-ep-jersey-44383 |publisher=J-14 |accessdate=October 16, 2014}}</ref> The lead single from the EP, "[[Call It Whatever (song)|Call It Whatever]]", debuted in the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] chart at number forty-seven, eventually rising to number ten, spending a total of ten weeks on the chart.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/call-it-whatever-single/id872799484 |title=Bella Thorne – Call It Whatever – Single |date=May 14, 2014 |publisher=[[iTunes]] |accessdate=May 16, 2014}}</ref><ref name=Billboard>{{cite web |author=Jason Lipshutz |title=Bella Thorne Talks 'Call It Whatever' Single & Unfair Comparisons To Other Disney Stars |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6092216/bella-thorne-interview-call-it-whatever-disney-album-tour |website=billboard.com |accessdate=June 15, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idolator.com/7517990/bella-thorne-call-it-whatever-cover-producer |title=Bella Thorne Unveils The Cover Of Debut Single ''Call It Whatever'', Announces Release Date |date=May 12, 2014 |author=Mike Wass |publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |accessdate=May 16, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Music video">{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TciYA70POj0 |title=Bella Thorne - Call It Whatever (Official Video) |date=May 29, 2014 |publisher=Bella Thorne on [[Vevo]] ([[YouTube]]) |accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref><ref name=HotClub>{{cite web |author=Gary Trust |title=Chart Highlights: U2 Makes History Atop Adult Alternative Songs, Taylor Swift Tops AC |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6312227/chart-highlights-u2-makes-history-atop-adult-alternative-songs |publisher=Billboard |accessdate=January 3, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=2015-03-01: Dance Club Songs |url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2015-01-03/dance-club-play-songs |publisher=Billboard |accessdate=January 3, 2015}}</ref>

It was reported that Thorne had signed a new deal to write a series of books, beginning with her first novel, ''Autumn Falls''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2013/05/05/bella-thorne-begins-writing-her-autumn-falls-novel |title=Bella Thorne Begins Writing Her "Autumn Falls" Novel |publisher=Disney Dreaming |accessdate=October 11, 2013}}</ref> Thorne has signed on as one of the leads in Manis Film's thriller ''Big Sky''; Thorne plays Hazel.<ref name=deadlinesky>{{cite web |url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/10/bella-thorne-kyra-sedgwick-big-sky-movie-casting |title=Bella Thorne & Kyra Sedgwick Set For Thriller 'Big Sky' |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=October 11, 2013}}</ref> On December 12, Thorne was cast in the MTV series ''[[Scream (TV series)|Scream]]'', which is a [[television adaptation]] based on the original [[slasher film]] series ''[[Scream (film series)|Scream]]''.<ref name=BellaThorneCasted>{{cite web |author=Samantha Highfill |title=Bella Thorne says she'll play Drew Barrymore's part in MTV's 'Scream' |url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2014/12/11/bella-thorne-scream-mtv |publisher=Inside TV |accessdate=December 12, 2014}}</ref> Thorne was offered the lead role of the series but felt that the role of the "mean, terrible Nina" would be more iconic.<ref>[http://hollywoodlife.com/2015/06/18/bella-thorne-scream-role-turned-down-lead-main-character/ Bella Thorne Reveals She Was Offered Lead On ‘Scream': Why She Turned It Down], hollywoodlife.com, June 18, 2015; accessed January 7, 2016.</ref> In 2015, Thorne was cast in the animated U.S. dub of the film ''[[The Frog Kingdom]]'', portraying the role of Frog Princess. The film is scheduled to be released on [[video on demand]] and on DVD beginning on June 30, 2015, by [[Lionsgate Home Entertainment]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fef5o2vKyyo |title=Frog Kingdom Official Trailer 1 (2015) - Rob Schneider Animated Movie HD |publisher=YouTube |date=April 27, 2015 |accessdate=January 8, 2016}}</ref>

On June 1, 2015, it was announced that Thorne would star in the [[AwesomenessTV]] film ''[[Shovel Buddies]]'', playing the role of Kate, the movie was released on iTunes in October 11, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |author=Patrick Hipes |url=http://deadline.com/2015/06/bella-thorne-shovel-buddies-cast-1201435625/ |title=Bella Thorne To Star In 'Shovel Buddies' At Awesomeness TV — Film Briefs |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=June 1, 2015 |accessdate=January 8, 2016}}</ref> She will also play Jamie, a disillusioned teenager intensely guarding a personal secret, in the film ''[[Keep Watching]]''.<ref name=keepw>{{cite web |author=Beatrice Verhoeven |url=http://www.thewrap.com/bella-thornes-keep-watching-picked-up-by-screen-gems/ |title=Bella Thorne's Home Invasion Thriller 'Keep Watching' Lands at Screen Gems |work=[[TheWrap]] |date=October 30, 2015|access-date=March 25, 2017}}</ref>

Also in 2015, she appeared as Ashley, a young and famous singer in ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Road Chip]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2015/03/bella-thorne-alvin-and-the-chipmunks-jon-bernthal-richard-armitage-tom-holland-pilgrimage-1201395541/ |title=Bella Thorne Squirrels Away 'Chipmunks 4' Role; Three Join 'Pilgrimage'; 108 Media Acquires 'Below Dreams' |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |author=Erik Pedersen |date=March 23, 2015}}</ref> In 2016, Thorne played Rain in Tyler Perry's ''[[Boo! A Madea Halloween]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2016/03/lionsgate-drops-teaser-trailer-for-tyler-perrys-madea-halloween-movie-boo-bitches-153025/|title=Lionsgate Drops Teaser-Trailer for Tyler Perry's 'Madea' Halloween Movie – "Boo Bitches!"|first=Tambay A.|last=Obenson|date=March 4, 2016|website=indiewire.com|accessdate=August 8, 2018}}</ref>

In 2017, Thorne went back to television with a drama series ''[[Famous in Love]]'' airing on Freeform where she played Paige Townsen, an ordinary college student, who gets her big break after auditioning for the starring role in a Hollywood blockbuster. In the same year, Thorne starred in the [[Netflix]] original film, ''[[You Get Me (film)|You Get Me]]''. In October of that year, Thorne appeared in the slasher comedy ''[[The Babysitter (2017 film)|The Babysitter]]'', directed by [[McG]] and released directly to Netflix.

Thorne stars in the romantic drama ''[[Midnight Sun (2018 film)|Midnight Sun]]'', based on the 2006 Japanese film of the same name. The film was released on March 23, 2018.

In August 2018, it was revealed that Thorne has officially returned to music and signed to [[Epic Records]] and began work on her debut album titled, ''What Do You See Now?'', which is expected to release in late 2018.<ref name=Rapper>{{cite web |author=Mike Wass |title=Bella Thorne's Rap Album Is Called What Do You See Now|url=http://www.idolator.com/7681320/bella-thorne-rap-album-what-do-you-see-now?andro=1&chrome=1&ios=1&safari=1 |publisher=Hive Media Group |accessdate=July 15, 2018}}</ref>

==Philanthropy==
Thorne is an avid supporter of the [[The Humane Society of the United States|Humane Society]], the [[Cystic Fibrosis Foundation]], and The Nomad Organization, which provides education, food and medical supplies to children in Africa.<ref name="Disney Channel Medianet"/>  She also joined [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals|PETA]] in encouraging people to boycott and protest [[SeaWorld]], acknowledging that as a child she appeared in a commercial for the theme park.<ref>Scott Baumgartner, "Bella Thorne Stars In Anti-SeaWorld Spot That Addresses Her Childhood Ad For the Amusement Park," [https://www.etonline.com/bella-thorne-stars-in-anti-seaworld-spot-that-addresses-her-childhood-ad-for-the-amusement-park ET] July 23, 2018.</ref>

==Personal life==

In August 2016, Thorne [[Coming out|came out]] as [[Bisexuality|bisexual]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Mike Vulpo |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/789636/bella-thorne-grateful-for-all-the-accepting-messages-after-revealing-she-is-bisexual |title=Bella Thorne Grateful for All the "Accepting" Messages After Revealing She Is Bisexual |work=E News! |date=August 23, 2016 |accessdate=August 23, 2016}}</ref> She has been in a relationship with [[internet personality]] [[Tana Mongeau]] since the summer of 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2018/10/18/bella-thorne-dating-both-tana-mongeau-mod-sun-interview/|title=Bella Thorne Admits She’s Dating Both Mod Sun & Tana Mongeau In Tell-All New Interview|last=Brow|first=Jason|date=October 18, 2018|work=Hollywood Life|access-date=November 18, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> She was previously in a relationship with late rapper [[Lil Peep]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gabe |first1=Bergado |title=Bella Thorne Spotted Kissing Rapper Lil Peep |url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/bella-thorne-kissing-lil-peep |accessdate=November 18, 2018 |publisher=Teen Vogue |date=September 13, 2017}}</ref>

