{{Infobox CFL player |name=Bob Kosid |birth_date={{birth date and age|1942|2|27}} |birth_place=[[Brandon, Manitoba]] |death_date= |death_place= |status=Retired |import=no |Height_ft=5 |Height_in=10 |Weight_lbs=185 |position1=Defensive back |career_highlights= * Grey Cup champion ({{CFL Year|1966}}) |CFLWestAllStar= |Awards= |Records= |playing_years1=1964&ndash;1972 |playing_team1=[[Saskatchewan Roughriders]] |CollegeHOF= |CFHOF= |CFHOFYear= }} '''Bob Kosid''' (born February 27, 1942) is a retired [[Canadian football]] player who played for the [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]]. He won the [[Grey Cup]] with Saskatchewan in 1966.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.canada.com/story.html?id=ec674b38-dc09-401e-b206-0bbc0e3d4e1b |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-04-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160324101628/http://www.canada.com/story.html?id=ec674b38-dc09-401e-b206-0bbc0e3d4e1b |archivedate=2016-03-24 |df= }}</ref><ref>http://www.justsportsstats.com/footballstatsindex.php?player_id=kosidbob001</ref> He is an alumnus of the [[University of Kentucky]].
