{{Infobox person | image = | caption = | birth_date ={{birth date|1959|09|16}} | birth_place = Upland, California | death_date = {{death date and age|2013|02|19|1959|09|16|mf=y}} | death_place = Austin, Texas | occupation = [[actor]] }}
'''Gary Poulter''' (September 16, 1959 - February 19, 2013) was a street performer<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/06/movies/nicolas-cage-returns-to-indie-essentials-with-joe.html|title=Nicolas Cage Returns to Indie Essentials With ‘Joe’|first=Robert|last=Ito|date=4 April 2014|accessdate=September 6, 2017 |publisher=''The New York Times''}}</ref> and an American actor known for his lead role alongside [[Nicolas Cage]] in [[David Gordon Green|David Gordon Green's]] 2013 film ''[[Joe (2013 film)|Joe]]''. Poulter was homeless, living on the streets of Austin, Texas when he was cast in the role of Wade, the abusive alcoholic father of Gary, played by [[Tye Sheridan]].<ref name=OConnell>{{cite web | url=http://www.austinchronicle.com/screens/2014-04-11/his-name-was-gary-poulter/ | title=His Name Was Gary Poulter | work=Austin Chronicle | date=April 11, 2014 | accessdate=February 14, 2015 | author=O'Connell, Joe}}</ref><ref name=Macnab>{{cite web | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/gary-poultner-from-homeless-breakdancer-to-starring-alongside-nicolas-cage-in-joe-9633394.html | title=Gary Poultner: From homeless breakdancer to starring alongside Nicolas Cage in Joe | work=The Independent | date=July 28, 2014 | accessdate=February 14, 2015 | author=Macnab, Geoffrey}}</ref><ref name=HO>{{cite web | url=http://www.hollywoodoutbreak.com/2014/04/10/nicolas-cage-reflects-on-late-and-talented-joe-co-star-gary-poulter/ | title="Joe" Star Gary Poulter Remembered By Nicolas Cage | work=Hollywood Outbreak | accessdate=February 14, 2015}}</ref><ref name=Labrecque>{{cite web | url=http://www.ew.com/article/2013/09/14/toronto-nicolas-cage-gary-poulter-joe | title=Toronto: The sad, tragic story of the homeless-man scene-stealer in Nicolas Cage's movie, 'Joe' | work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] | date=September 14, 2013 | accessdate=February 14, 2015 | author=Labrecque, Jeff}}</ref><ref name=Juzwiak>{{cite web |url=http://gawker.com/the-tragedy-of-gary-poulter-nic-cages-homeless-co-sta-1562031788 |title=The Tragedy of Gary Poulter, Nic Cage's Homeless Co-Star |work=[[Gawker]] |date=April 11, 2014 |accessdate=February 14, 2015 |author=Juzwiak, Rich |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150210002011/http://gawker.com/the-tragedy-of-gary-poulter-nic-cages-homeless-co-sta-1562031788 |archivedate=February 10, 2015 |df= }}</ref>
==Early life== Poulter grew up in [[Upland, California]]. At 17, he joined the Navy and served on a ship in Japan. He went AWOL for 1-1/2 years in Japan and ultimately was court-martialed in [[Washington, D.C.]], whereupon he received a [[Military discharge|dishonorable discharge]].<ref name=OConnell/>
==Film role== In 2013, Poulter was recruited from the streets of Austin to play the third lead, "Wade", in the film ''Joe'', which became his sole film performance, although he worked as a background extra in 1987 in the TV series ''[[Thirtysomething]]''. Shortly before landing the film role, Poulter worked for a traveling carnival, but he was left naked on the side of the road after he was caught stealing money.<ref name=OConnell/>
===Reviews=== ''[[The Independent]]'' summed up Poulter's performance in its movie review, writing, "In his only screen role, he offers an utterly compelling portrait of a man so consumed by self-loathing that he will go to extreme lengths to destroy the life of his son."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/reviews/joe-film-review-nicolas-cage-delivers-an-astonishing-performance-in-low-budget-drama-9627270.html|title=Joe, film review: Nicolas Cage delivers an astonishing performance in|author=|date=24 July 2014|publisher=}}</ref>
Movie critic Peter Sobczynski in his review for [[RogerEbert.com]] described Poulter's film debut as a "stunning performance" and "one of the great one-shot performances in the history of the cinema."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/joe-2014|title=Joe Movie Review & Film Summary (2014) - Roger Ebert|first=Peter|last=Sobczynski|date=|website=www.rogerebert.com}}</ref>
===Award=== The [[Austin Film Critics Association]] gave Poulter the Special Honorary Award in 2014 for his performance in ''Joe''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://austinfilmcritics.org/2014-awards-5d1c9a372b9f|title=2014 Awards – Austin Film Critics Association|author=|date=7 December 2016|publisher=}}</ref>
==Death== Before the film's 2014 release, Poulter was found dead on February 10, 2013, at the edge of [[Lady Bird Lake]], a river-like reservoir in Austin, Texas.<ref name=OConnell/> Director Green dedicated the film ''Joe'' to Poulter.<ref name=Labrecque/>
