'''Édouard S. Léger''' (May 27, 1890 – 1971) was a [[Canada|Canadian]] businessman and politician in the [[New Brunswick|Province of New Brunswick]].

Léger was first elected to the [[Legislative Assembly of New Brunswick|Legislative Assembly]] in the [[New Brunswick general election, 1939|1939 New Brunswick general election]] as the [[New Brunswick Liberal Association|Liberal Party]] candidate in the multi-member riding of [[Westmorland County, New Brunswick|Westmorland County]]. He was reelected in [[New Brunswick general election, 1944|1944]] and again in [[New Brunswick general election, 1948|1948]]. He died in 1971.<ref>http://www.genealogie-acadienne.net/?action=indiDetails&I=38193</ref>

